explanation: This solution iterates through the typed string, checking if the current character matches the next character in the name string. If it does, it moves to the next character in the name string. If it doesn't, it checks if the current character in the typed string is the same as the previous one. If it's not, it returns False. If it iterates through the entire typed string and the index in the name string is equal to the length of the name string, it returns True. This approach has a high efficiency because it only requires a single pass through the typed string and a constant amount of space.

